description.narrative: By 2025, key child protection actors have in place a resilient child protection system relevant in development and humanitarian contexts with protective, promotive and responsive services that protect children from violence, exploitation, abuse and harmful practices., which contributes to Access To Justice, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 'By 2025, children in Ethiopia in both development and humanitarian contexts have legal identity and are safe and protected from violence, exploitation, abuse and harmful practices.
